@node Features "HNet V1.0: Features"
@{b}Features@{ub}

HNet is a network program used to connect two Amigas, like DNet, ProNet and
so on...

@{"I" link I} wrote this mainly because @{"I" link I} couldn`t get @{"DNet" link DNet} to work too well over a
3-Wire serial cable. @{"ProNet" link ProNet} seems to crash everytime someting goes wrong.

Features:

        * No crashes.

        * Easy @{"installation" link Inst}.

	* Small.

        * 32-Bit Checksum.

This program has been tested with:

        * An @{"Amiga" link Amiga} 1200 with a @{"Blizzard" link Blizzard} 1230 50 MHz.

	* An @{"Amiga" link Amiga}  4000/030 33MHz

        * A 7-Wire serial cable.

@endnode

@node Inst "HNet V1.0: Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

@{b}Just double-click the install icon!@{ub}

Or if you wat to do it the hard way:

   1. Create a directory somewhere on your harddrive.

   2. Make a assign to that directory called "HNT:" in your startup-sequence.

   3. Copy the files "@{"NChat" link NChat}" and "@{"EchoS" link EchoS}", from the bin directory, to HNT:.

   4. Copy the rest of the files in bin, and putthem somewhere in your path.

   5. Done!

@endnode

@node EchoS "HNet V1.0: EchoS"
@{b}EchoS@{ub}

EchoS (EchoString) is a server that is started whenever a program on the
remote computer needs to display a textstring. This is started by the
"@{"Exec" link Exec}" program when it is needed, and it will quit 100 seconds after the
last time it was used.
@endnode

@node NChat "HNet V1.0: NChat"

@{b}NChat@{ub}

NChat (NetChat) is a utility to communicate (chat) with the operator of the
other computer. Simply type "NChat" in a CLI prompt to start it.

Function keys in NChat:

F1 - Send a BEEP.

F2 - Clear buffer.

F3 - Clear Screen.

@endnode

@node Exec "HNet V1.0: Exec"

@{b}Exec@{ub}

The Exec program is the part of HNet that executes commands sent from the
other computer. This is started by the "@{"startnet" link StartNet}" script.
@endnode

@node StartNet "HNet V1.0: StartNet"

@{b}StartNet@{ub}

This script file should be located in the util directory, and is used to
start the network. If you get an error message telling you that the file is 
not executable, do this:

1.Workbench:HNet> @{b}protect util/startnet +s@{ub}

This will set the script flag, wich some archivers resets. If you don't do
this you will have to use Execute to run it.

The file runs "@{"Main" link Main}" and "@{"Exec" link Exec}.

@endnode

@node Main "HNet V1.0: Main"

@{b}Main@{ub}

This is the main network program that takes care of all the serial
communication, and sends the recieved data further to "@{"Exec" link Exec}".

@endnode

